7 NEW SECTION. Section 4. Judicial performance evaluations. (1) Beginning in 2026, the
8 commission shall prepare:
9 (a) a midterm performance evaluation for each district court judge during the third year of the
10 judge’s term;
11 (b) a preelection performance evaluation for each district court judge during the fifth year of the
12 judge's term;
13 (c) a midterm performance evaluation for each justice of the Montana supreme court during the
14 third year of the justice’s term;
15 (d) a preelection performance evaluation for each supreme court justice during the seventh year of
16 the justice's term; and
17 (e) a preelection performance evaluation for each judge appointed to a vacancy during the year
18 prior to the last year of the judge's current term.
19 (2) The performance evaluation for a judge under subsection (1) may consider only the information
20 listed in subsections (3) and (4). The performance evaluation must give primary emphasis to information
21 gathered since the judge's election or appointment to the judge's current term in office.
22 (3) The information a performance evaluation must consider is as follows:
23 (a) the results of the judge’s most recent judicial performance survey conducted in accordance
24 with [section 5];
25 (b) information acquired by observation of the judge's conduct in the courtroom;
26 (c) the judge’s judicial disciplinary record, if any;
